modules.description: Provides functions to serialize and deserialize BAP intermediate representation data using the PIQ format. Works with BAP's core data structures such as instructions, expressions, and memory regions. Used to persist and load program analysis results for debugging and binary inspection.

Converts between formatted BAP intermediate language (BIL) representations and S-expressions, enabling serialization and deserialization. Works with BAP's `bil`, `stmt`, `exp`, and `var` types, as well as Piqi-based representations of expressions and variables. Parses and generates BIL strings, BAP expressions, and statements from various format specifications.

Converts between formatted strings and Bap.Std program elements like functions, basic blocks, arguments, and definitions. Processes terms representing control flow graph nodes and their attributes. Used for parsing and serializing low-level intermediate representation data in reverse engineering tasks.
